---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { SOCIAL } from '../consts';
import flyingPhoto from '../assets/about/jeremy-flying.jpeg';
---
<BaseLayout title="About" description="About Jeremy Winterberg — software engineer.">
  <h1>About</h1>
  <p>I'm a software engineer with over a decade of experience building and scaling
    full-stack platforms — robust distributed systems, the APIs on top of them, and
    the infrastructure underneath. I work most in Ruby on Rails, AWS, and Postgres,
    and spend my side-project time in Go, TypeScript, React, and Next.js.</p>

  <h2>Experience</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Senior Software Engineer — PrimeTrust</strong> (2021–2023). Built
      and scaled a core financial API, cut p95 latency on ~500k daily requests from
      20s to under 500ms, and led a Heroku→AWS migration on Kubernetes, Terraform,
      and ArgoCD with 100% uptime.</li>
    <li><strong>Senior Software Engineer — Smartcare Software</strong> (2019–2021).
      Migrated systems to AWS (99.99% availability, ~$50k/yr saved) and architected
      integrations for nationwide electronic visit verification.</li>
    <li><strong>Software Engineer — Consulting</strong> (2017–2019). Delivered Rails
      and Angular applications for clients including the University of Minnesota.</li>
    <li><strong>Ruby on Rails Developer — UW–Eau Claire</strong> (2015–2017).</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Skills</h2>
  <p><strong>Languages:</strong> Ruby, Go, TypeScript, SQL.
    <strong>Frameworks:</strong> Ruby on Rails, React, Next.js, Angular.
    <strong>Platforms &amp; tools:</strong> AWS, Docker, Kubernetes, Terraform,
    GitHub Actions, DataDog, Postgres, Redis.</p>

  <h2>Education</h2>
  <p>BSc Computer Science, University of Wisconsin–Eau Claire (minor: Economics).</p>

  <h2>Off the clock: aviation</h2>
  <figure class="about-photo">
    <Image src={flyingPhoto} alt="Jeremy at the controls of a small aircraft, wearing an aviation headset" width={320} densities={[1, 2]} />
  </figure>
  <p>When I'm not at a keyboard, you'll usually find me at the airport. I earned my
    private pilot certificate in 2023, and flying has become one of my favorite ways
    to think, reset, and see the world from a different altitude. A lot of what makes
    aviation work — checklists, systems thinking, and managing risk deliberately —
    quietly makes me a better engineer, too.</p>

  <p>For the full work history, see my <a href={SOCIAL.linkedin} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">LinkedIn</a>,
    and my code on <a href={SOCIAL.github} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a>.</p>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about-photo { margin: 1.25rem 0; }
  .about-photo :global(img) {
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    max-width: 320px;
    height: auto;
    border-radius: 12px;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 16px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.15);
  }
</style>
